      <odd id="aspace_ea6642bd3cf3be970511eefbd559eadc">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 37 (YRG 37), Records of associations, institutes, centers, and organizations affiliated with Yale University.</p>  
      </odd>
      <altformavail id="aspace_fa6eca84646caa544d333bbfe035af5b">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>The entire collection is also available on microfilm (442 frames on 1 reel, 35mm.) from Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library, at cost. Order no. HM170.</p>  
      </altformavail>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_30e32bf928261322ac87f927c64523b6">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
         <p>Patrons must use FILM HM 170 instead of the originals.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_fc147c9b1169645001f676126b1c4baa">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>New Haven County Medical Society Records (RU 485). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_81c32560f252e54cda8416dec5512448">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by record type.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_2ca88dc939e76ca9f60c9b635877d2de">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of minutes and tax and statistics books documenting the operations and activities of the New Haven County Medical Association, which formed in 1784 as the Medical Society of New-Haven County.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
